## root
Usage: harness-kit [options] [command]

AI-friendly repo harness

Options:
  -V, --version                    output the version number
  -h, --help                       display help for command

Commands:
  init [options]                   scaffold .agents/ skeleton + starter manifest
  sync [options]                   generate tool files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md)
                                   from manifest
  upgrade [options]                upgrade this repository to the running
                                   harness-kit version
  prepare-adoption [options]       render a private, repository-external
                                   candidate bundle for blind legacy review
  record-adoption-audit [options]  record a declared pass/fail review receipt
                                   bound to one adoption candidate and report
  doctor [options]                 dev-time health check: completeness, drift,
                                   freshness, tech debt
  verify [options]                 CI gate: run enforceable invariants +
                                   contracts + drift; nonzero on failure
  plan-checks [options]            compute which declared checks THIS change
                                   should run (impact-driven, executes nothing)
  task [options]                   manage the worktree task base used by deliver
                                   (optional; SessionStart also sets it)
  task-start [options]             record task-start base SHA for this worktree
                                   so deliver covers later commits
  deliver [options]                accept this task change: resolve scope →
                                   run-checks + verify → stamp (preferred finish
                                   gate)
  run-checks [options]             plan + run resolved checks; record evidence;
                                   nonzero on failure/unresolved blocking gap
  evidence [options]               show the latest durable delivery stamp /
                                   run-checks evidence for this worktree/session
  record-context-review [options]  record an Agent's completed review of one
                                   knowledge item or module against its bound
                                   sources
  accept-contract [options]        record current contract fingerprint(s) as the
                                   accepted baseline (after an intended change)
  install-hooks [options]          install git hooks and/or agent SessionStart +
                                   Stop hooks (run-checks + verify gate)
  onboard                          print the erzhe-harness-init skill for an
                                   agent to follow (use via npx, always latest)
  check-loop                       print the harness-check-loop skill: the
                                   implement -> verify loop for an agent
  help [command]                   display help for command

## init
Usage: harness-kit init [options]

scaffold .agents/ skeleton + starter manifest

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --name <name>     project name (default: "my-project")
  --force           overwrite existing manifest (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## prepare-adoption
Usage: harness-kit prepare-adoption [options]

render a private, repository-external candidate bundle for blind legacy review

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --out <dir>       new or empty output directory outside the repository
  --json            machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## record-adoption-audit
Usage: harness-kit record-adoption-audit [options]

record a declared pass/fail review receipt bound to one adoption candidate and
report

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>       target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --candidate <dir>      prepared adoption bundle outside the repository
  --verdict <pass|fail>  declared audit verdict
  --report <file>        independent audit report to hash and bind
  --reason <text>        non-empty reviewer rationale
  --out <receipt>        receipt path outside the repository (default: candidate
                         bundle)
  --json                 machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help             display help for command

## sync
Usage: harness-kit sync [options]

generate tool files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md) from manifest

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>   target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --adopt-existing   apply only a content-bound, pass-attested legacy adoption
                     (default: false)
  --candidate <dir>  prepared adoption bundle outside the repository
  --audit <receipt>  pass audit receipt bound to the candidate bundle
  -h, --help         display help for command

## upgrade
Usage: harness-kit upgrade [options]

upgrade this repository to the running harness-kit version

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --check           read-only; exit 2 when an upgrade is available (default:
                    false)
  --json            machine-readable single-report output (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## doctor
Usage: harness-kit doctor [options]

dev-time health check: completeness, drift, freshness, tech debt

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --details         show every declared verification boundary and maintenance
                    action (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## verify
Usage: harness-kit verify [options]

CI gate: run enforceable invariants + contracts + drift; nonzero on failure

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --json            machine-readable output (default: false)
  --details         show every declared verification boundary and maintenance
                    action (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## task
Usage: harness-kit task [options]

manage the worktree task base used by deliver (optional; SessionStart also sets
it)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --json            machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## task-start
Usage: harness-kit task-start [options]

record task-start base SHA for this worktree so deliver covers later commits

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>      override base (default: current HEAD)
  --note <text>     optional task note
  --json            machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## deliver
Usage: harness-kit deliver [options]

accept this task change: resolve scope → run-checks + verify → stamp (preferred
finish gate)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>      target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>          explicit task base (overrides task record)
  --profile <checkset>  use a validation.checksets entry instead of per-module
                        checks
  --json                machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help            display help for command

## plan-checks
Usage: harness-kit plan-checks [options]

compute which declared checks THIS change should run (impact-driven, executes
nothing)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>      target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>          diff base (default: working tree + untracked vs HEAD)
                        (default: "HEAD")
  --profile <checkset>  use a validation.checksets entry instead of per-module
                        checks
  --json                machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help            display help for command

## run-checks
Usage: harness-kit run-checks [options]

plan + run resolved checks; record evidence; nonzero on failure/unresolved
blocking gap

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>      target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>          task-start ref; required for manual proof after task
                        changes were committed
  --profile <checkset>  use a validation.checksets entry instead of per-module
                        checks
  --waive <kind>        waive one eligible coverage gap for this exact change
                        fingerprint
  --where <scope>       exact gap scope; required when a kind matches multiple
                        gaps
  --reason <text>       reason recorded with --waive
  --session <token>     validation session token (normally supplied by an agent
                        hook)
  --json                machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help            display help for command

## evidence
Usage: harness-kit evidence [options]

show the latest durable delivery stamp / run-checks evidence for this
worktree/session

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>   target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --session <token>  specific validation session token
  --json             machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help         display help for command

## record-context-review
Usage: harness-kit record-context-review [options]

record an Agent's completed review of one knowledge item or module against its
bound sources

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>         target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --path <knowledge-path>  exact knowledge.path from the manifest
  --module <name>          exact module name (mutually exclusive with --path)
  --reason <text>          what was reviewed and why the context remains correct
  --session <token>        Agent/session identifier to keep with the review
                           evidence
  --json                   machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help               display help for command

## accept-contract
Usage: harness-kit accept-contract [options]

record current contract fingerprint(s) as the accepted baseline (after an
intended change)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --id <id>         only this contract (default: all with a snapshot command)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## install-hooks
Usage: harness-kit install-hooks [options]

install git hooks and/or agent SessionStart + Stop hooks (run-checks + verify
gate)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>          target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --git                     install git hooks (default when no selector given)
  --stop                    install agent SessionStart + Stop hooks (Claude Code
                            / Cursor / Codex)
  --agents <list>           comma list of agent tools for --stop:
                            claude,cursor,codex (default: all)
  --force                   refresh harness-kit-managed hooks; never overwrite
                            foreign hooks (default: false)
  --allow-shared-git-hooks  acknowledge native hooks affect every linked
                            worktree (default: false)
  --allow-user-dispatcher   allow the safe CODEX_HOME dispatcher required by
                            Codex in linked worktrees (default: false)
  -h, --help                display help for command

## onboard
Usage: harness-kit onboard [options]

print the erzhe-harness-init skill for an agent to follow (use via npx, always
latest)

Options:
  -h, --help  display help for command

## check-loop
Usage: harness-kit check-loop [options]

print the harness-check-loop skill: the implement -> verify loop for an agent

Options:
  -h, --help  display help for command
